(43, 13, 16, 43, 15, 20, 20, 'The servant is not greater than his lord', 'Servanthood and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that the servant is not greater than the lord, linking the concept of servanthood to the experience of persecution. This connection highlights that just as Jesus faced persecution, his followers will also encounter similar challenges.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 16, 40, 10, 24, 25, 'the servant is not greater than his lord', 'Servanthood and Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between a master and his servant, highlighting that the disciple is not above his master. This connection underscores the expectation of humility and shared experience in servanthood.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 16, 43, 3, 5, 5, NULL, 'Servanthood and Spiritual Birth', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility and the necessity of spiritual rebirth. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing one''s position in relation to God and the transformative process required to enter the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
