(43, 13, 17, 59, 1, 25, 25, 'happy are ye if ye do them', 'Connection of Blessing and Action', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of action in relation to knowledge. John 13:17 states that happiness comes from doing, while James 1:25 highlights that being a doer leads to blessings.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 17, 40, 7, 24, 25, 'happy are ye if ye do them', 'Connection of Obedience and Wisdom', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doing what is taught. John 13:17 states that happiness comes from doing, while Matthew 7:24-25 likens obedience to building on a solid foundation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 17, 2, 40, 16, 16, 'happy are ye if ye do them', 'Obedience and Happiness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to God''s commands. John highlights the happiness that comes from doing what is known, while Exodus illustrates Moses'' adherence to God''s instructions.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 17, 26, 36, 27, 27, 'do them', 'Connection of Obedience and Joy', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doing God''s commands. John highlights happiness in knowing and doing, while Ezekiel speaks of the Spirit enabling obedience to God''s statutes.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 17, 42, 12, 47, 48, 'happy are ye if ye do them', 'Connection of Knowledge and Action', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing and doing one''s duty. John 13:17 highlights the happiness that comes from doing what one knows, while Luke 12:47-48 stresses the consequences of failing to act on that knowledge. This connection highlights the responsibility that comes with understanding.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 18, 19, 41, 9, 9, 'hath lifted up his heel against me', 'Betrayal by a Close Friend', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal by a trusted companion. Both passages refer to a familiar friend who has dined with the speaker and subsequently turned against them.', 'theme', 0.7409999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 18, 40, 26, 23, 23, 'eateth bread with me', 'Betrayal and Shared Meal', 'Both passages emphasize betrayal by a close associate during a meal. The phrase ''eateth bread with me'' in John connects to ''dippeth his hand with me in the dish'' in Matthew, highlighting the intimate nature of the betrayal.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 18, 43, 17, 12, 12, 'that the scripture may be fulfilled', 'Connection of Betrayal and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of betrayal among Jesus'' chosen followers. The phrase ''that the scripture may be fulfilled'' links the acknowledgment of betrayal in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 18, 41, 14, 20, 20, 'He that eateth bread with me', 'Betrayal by a Disciple', 'Both passages emphasize the betrayal of Jesus by one of his chosen disciples. John 13:18 mentions the act of eating bread, while Mark 14:20 highlights the one who dips with Jesus in the dish, indicating the same act of betrayal.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 18, 43, 13, 26, 26, 'He that eateth bread with me', 'Connection of Betrayal Theme', 'Both passages emphasize betrayal, as indicated by ''He that eateth bread with me hath lifted up his heel against me'' in the source verse, which foreshadows Judas''s actions in the target passage. The act of Jesus giving the sop to Judas highlights the fulfillment of this betrayal.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 18, 40, 10, 36, 36, 'He that eateth bread with me', 'Betrayal and Familial Conflict', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal within close relationships. Both passages emphasize how those closest to an individual can become adversaries, as seen in the betrayal of Jesus by a close companion and the conflict within one''s own household.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 18, 58, 4, 13, 13, 'He that eateth bread with me', 'Insight into Divine Awareness', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal and divine knowledge. In John 13:18, the act of betrayal is revealed, while Hebrews 4:13 emphasizes that all actions are visible to God. Both passages underscore the awareness of God regarding human actions.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 19, 23, 43, 10, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''I am he,'' linking the identity of God with the assurance of belief. This connection highlights the importance of recognizing God''s true nature and the call to witness that truth.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 19, 43, 14, 29, 29, NULL, 'Connection of Foretelling Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the act of telling beforehand to strengthen belief when events occur. The repetition of the phrase ''before it come to pass'' underscores this theme of prophetic revelation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 19, 43, 16, 4, 4, 'when it is come to pass', 'Foretelling and Remembrance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prior warnings. In John 13:19, Jesus indicates that he tells them beforehand to strengthen their belief, while John 16:4 highlights that he shares these things so they may remember them later.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 19, 66, 1, 17, 18, 'I am he', 'Connection of Identity and Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as ''I am he,'' providing assurance of His divine authority. John 13:19 prepares believers for the fulfillment of His words, while Revelation 1:17-18 affirms His eternal existence and power over death.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 19, 23, 48, 5, 5, NULL, 'Prophetic Revelation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of foretelling events. Both passages emphasize the declaration of future occurrences to affirm belief and prevent misattribution to idols.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
